# Documentation Standards

## Document Frontmatter (Required)
```yaml
---
epoch: 2025.10.E1
doc: relative/path/to/file.md
owner: {agent-name}
created: YYYY-MM-DD
last_reviewed: YYYY-MM-DD
doc_hash: TBD
expires: YYYY-MM-DD
---
```

## Documentation Types

### Direction Files
Location: [docs/directions/](mdc:docs/directions/)
- Agent-specific priorities
- START HERE NOW section
- Canon references
- Task lists with estimates
- Timeline expectations

### Runbooks
Location: [docs/runbooks/](mdc:docs/runbooks/)
- Step-by-step procedures
- Incident response plans
- Deployment checklists
- Recovery procedures

### Design Docs
Location: [docs/design/](mdc:docs/design/)
- UI/UX specifications
- Voice & tone guides
- Copy audits
- Localization analysis

### Evidence
Location: [docs/compliance/evidence/](mdc:docs/compliance/evidence/)
- Timestamped artifacts
- Incident documentation
- Audit trails
- Action item tracking

## Formatting Standards

### Headings
```markdown
# H1 - Document Title
## H2 - Major Sections
### H3 - Subsections
```

### Code Blocks
Always specify language:
```markdown
```typescript
// TypeScript code
```
```

### Tables
Use proper markdown tables with alignment

### Evidence Logging
Include:
- ISO 8601 timestamps
- Commands executed
- File locations
- Next steps

